{"id":"7116","name":"toggle flashlight","tagline":"Turn flashlight on/off without looking or touching the screen","icon":"ios14 c463140863 g59764","latest":"22122","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>In conjunction with iOS Back Tap functionality, this shortcut enables turning the flashlight on/off without looking or touching the screen. Just tap the back of the phone to turn it on then tap the back again to turn it off.</p>\n<p>‘cause sometimes you can’t get your eyes off what you’re trying to illuminate or your hands are nasty as hell and you don’t want to touch the delicate screen of your precious phone.</p>\n<p>The shortcut by itself just toggles flashlight on/off on subsequent calls. </p>\n<p>To run it with Back Tap:</p>\n<p>1) Go to: Settings &gt; Accessibility &gt; Touch &gt; Back Tap</p>\n<p>2) Set Double or Triple Tap to run this shortcut</p>\n<p>Note:</p>\n<p>Back Tap will only work if the iPhone screen is on, so if the screen is off, you’ll need to click any button or slightly twist the phone up to turn the screen on before back tapping.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>0.0.0 - Oct. 22, 2020, 12:18 a.m.</strong></p>"}